## Main purpose and functionality

The `voice_hal_getCountServices` function is used to retrieve the count of voice services present on the system.

## Key operations and data flow

The function takes no arguments and returns the count of voice services as an integer.

## Interaction with other components (if any)

This function interacts with the underlying voice hardware and software to retrieve the count of voice services.

## Important parameters and return values

The function takes no arguments and returns the count of voice services as an integer.

## Any specific RDK-related operations

This function is specific to RDK and is used to retrieve the count of voice services on an RDK system.
